    <node id="Convolutional Network Depth and Image Recognition Accuracy Study (text)">
      <data key="d0">Convolutional Network Depth and Image Recognition Accuracy Study (text)</data>
      <data key="d1">text</data>
      <data key="d2">This work analyzes the effect of convolutional network depth on accuracy in image recognition, demonstrating that increasing depth (16-19 layers) significantly improves performance. The findings were key to the ImageNet Challenge 2014 success, and the models developed are shared for further research in computer vision.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5dcc78c18bb24e5d3883bff880ea74b3</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858596</data>
    </node>
