    <node id="ConvNet Configuration Analysis (text)">
      <data key="d0">ConvNet Configuration Analysis (text)</data>
      <data key="d1">text</data>
      <data key="d2">The text analyzes ConvNet configurations, highlighting their differences from previous top-performing models in ILSVRC competitions. It emphasizes the use of small $3 \times 3$ receptive fields across the network, contrasting with the larger fields previously employed, and discusses the effective receptive field produced by stacking layers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-416b1d89ed7672b0cd4c2753ae95d9a8</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
