      <data key="d1">text</data>
      <data key="d2">This text discusses the evaluation of deep convolutional networks (up to 19 layers) for large-scale image classification, emphasizing that depth improves classification accuracy and achieves state-of-the-art performance on the ImageNet dataset. It highlights the models' good generalization capabilities and confirms the importance of depth in visual representations.</data>
