    <node id="Net-E">
      <data key="d0">Net-E</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Net-E is a deep learning model comparable to Net-D, evaluated on the ILSVRC dataset for classification performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Net-E is a neural network architecture that, along with Net-D, achieves identical performance on VOC datasets.&lt;SEP&gt;Net-E is another feature extraction model used alongside Net-D for improved image representation in action classification.&lt;SEP&gt;Net-E is a 19-layer neural network model that performs better than the 16-layer Net-D and improves performance when combined.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-40bfade9d2720e8c40f7ccada6980ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-75d1f552a2805d55c662bc781d1dfbb2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10bad65f675245d138aefe0373476c36&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a491b80f17cc8407c12dc3723276319</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858926</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Net-D">
      <data key="d0">Net-D</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Net-D is a deep learning model designed for classification tasks, with high performance on the ILSVRC dataset.&lt;SEP&gt;Net-D is a neural network architecture that exhibits performance comparable to Net-E on VOC datasets.&lt;SEP&gt;Net-D is a feature extraction model used to represent images, contributing to action classification performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Net-D is a 16-layer neural network model that is outperformed by Net-E and their combination.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-40bfade9d2720e8c40f7ccada6980ef7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-75d1f552a2805d55c662bc781d1dfbb2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10bad65f675245d138aefe0373476c36&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a491b80f17cc8407c12dc3723276319</data>
