    <node id="VOC-2012">
      <data key="d0">VOC-2012</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">VOC-2012 is another dataset for image classification evaluation, with mean AP scores for various methods.&lt;SEP&gt;VOC-2012 is a dataset used for image classification benchmarks with approximately 22,500 images annotated with labels across 20 object categories.&lt;SEP&gt;VOC-2012 is a dataset used for validation in image descriptor performance analysis.&lt;SEP&gt;VOC-2012 is a specific subset of VOC datasets used for evaluating object detection performance.&lt;SEP&gt;VOC-2012 is an image dataset used for object and action classification tasks, containing labeled images and multiple classes.&lt;SEP&gt;A dataset for visual object categorization and detection, used as the benchmark in the analysis.</data>
