    <node id="Training Image Size">
      <data key="d0">Training Image Size</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The concept of training image size refers to the size parameter 'S', representing the smallest side of an isotropically-rescaled training image used in ConvNet input processing.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a661234bc5d404231fbf23c25c0f103e</data>
