    <node id="Convolutional Neural Network">
      <data key="d0">Convolutional Neural Network</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A convolutional neural network (ConvNet) is a deep learning model used for processing images, which requires fixed-size input images as described in the content.&lt;SEP&gt;A class of deep learning neural networks that process data with grid-like topology, such as images, used here in the context of image evaluation strategies.&lt;SEP&gt;A Convolutional Neural Network (ConvNet) is a deep learning architecture designed for processing and classifying images.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-87402a1e4f355b9c0a09f090f3a60df6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-978a7e2e478746fb8097d20c2ae24e6a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbbd3487e1c203b44ae9611fe9d0a159</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858962</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Training Images">
      <data key="d0">Training Images</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Training images are larger images used to generate fixed-size crop images through rescaling and cropping as part of the preprocessing pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;Images used for training deep learning models, split into batches for processing on GPUs.&lt;SEP&gt;The dataset contains 4.6K training images labeled into 11 classes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-87402a1e4f355b9c0a09f090f3a60df6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5caa942ac874b82acabe79ff7f8da1cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10bad65f675245d138aefe0373476c36</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858962</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Rescaled Images">
      <data key="d0">Rescaled Images</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Rescaled images are larger images adjusted in size that serve as the source for cropping to generate input images for the ConvNet.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-87402a1e4f355b9c0a09f090f3a60df6</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858962</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Crop">
      <data key="d0">Crop</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A crop refers to a fixed-size portion of a larger image, obtained by randomly cropping from rescaled training images during preprocessing.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-87402a1e4f355b9c0a09f090f3a60df6</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858962</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="SGD">
      <data key="d0">SGD</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) is the optimization algorithm during which each crop is generated per image per iteration.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-87402a1e4f355b9c0a09f090f3a60df6</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858963</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Augmentation">
      <data key="d0">Augmentation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Augmentation refers to the techniques used to increase the diversity of training data, including random horizontal flipping and RGB color shift.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-87402a1e4f355b9c0a09f090f3a60df6</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
