      <data key="d0">Multi-Scale Aggregation</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Multi-scale aggregation involves computing image descriptors at various scales and combining these results to enhance recognition accuracy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-13c671232831711c90250ba5e0433558</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Validation Sets">
      <data key="d0">Validation Sets</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Validation sets are datasets used to evaluate the performance of image descriptor methods in experiments.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-13c671232831711c90250ba5e0433558</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Localization ConvNets">
      <data key="d0">Localization ConvNets</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Localization ConvNets are neural network models trained to perform object localization tasks, differing from classification ConvNets by using Euclidean loss instead of logistic regression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Classification ConvNets">
      <data key="d0">Classification ConvNets</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Classification ConvNets are neural network models trained to classify images, traditionally using logistic regression objectives.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ILSVRC-2014">
      <data key="d0">ILSVRC-2014</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">ILSVRC-2014 is the version of the ImageNet Large Scale Visual Recognition Challenge held in 2014.&lt;SEP&gt;ILSVRC-2014 is a major image classification challenge in computer vision, referenced in the context of benchmarking machine learning models.&lt;SEP&gt;ILSVRC-2014 is an annual image classification and localization competition, in which the training models were applied.&lt;SEP&gt;ILSVRC-2014 is an image recognition challenge where the VGG team competed and won the localization challenge.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb0d159c3ed83612608daea64febc962&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da8ee2c8e114e5fd70e1825eda841068&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8174de9af39f73b16a6c89416ba12cdc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-416b1d89ed7672b0cd4c2753ae95d9a8</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Model Scales">
      <data key="d0">Model Scales</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Scales $S = 2 5 6$ and $S=3 8 4$ denote different scales used for training localisation models.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ground-Truth">
      <data key="d0">Ground-Truth</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Ground-truth represents the actual bounding box parameters used for training and evaluation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Euclidean Loss">
      <data key="d0">Euclidean Loss</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Euclidean loss is used as the objective function in localisation ConvNets to penalize deviations of predicted bounding box parameters.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Logistic Regression">
      <data key="d0">Logistic Regression</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Logistic regression is the objective used in classification ConvNets, replaced by Euclidean loss in localization tasks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bounded Box">
      <data key="d0">Bounded Box</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Bounding box parameters are the predicted outputs of localization models, used to locate objects within images.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858992</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Regression Loss">
      <data key="d0">Regression Loss</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Regression loss, specifically Euclidean loss, is used to penalize deviations in predicted bounding box parameters during training.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5af3169afc1b617a801c2fc164adace2</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
