    <node id="Localization ConvNet">
      <data key="d0">Localization ConvNet</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Localization ConvNet is a neural network used for object localization in images, applied to the entire image to generate bounding box predictions.&lt;SEP&gt;The localisation ConvNet is a convolutional neural network employed to improve object localization performance in images.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fed433068f333767bf66e9a93a7e311c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5606f2995c1604364f903b6d6ea800f8</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858994</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Classification ConvNet">
      <data key="d0">Classification ConvNet</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Classification ConvNet is a neural network used to classify images, producing class score maps that are contrasted with localization outputs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fed433068f333767bf66e9a93a7e311c</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858994</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bounding Box Predictions">
      <data key="d0">Bounding Box Predictions</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Bounding box predictions are the output of the last fully-connected layer in the localization process, representing object locations.&lt;SEP&gt;Bounding box predictions are outputs in object detection that can be enhanced in spatial resolution by the offsets technique.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fed433068f333767bf66e9a93a7e311c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0eea5a170983a0751ecda38142b90a95</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858994</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Greedy Merging Procedure">
      <data key="d0">Greedy Merging Procedure</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">The greedy merging procedure is a method that combines spatially close bounding box predictions, averaging their coordinates and rating them based on class scores.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fed433068f333767bf66e9a93a7e311c</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858994</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Multiple ConvNets">
      <data key="d0">Multiple ConvNets</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Multiple ConvNets refer to the use of more than one localization network, whose bounding box predictions are combined via union before merging.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fed433068f333767bf66e9a93a7e311c</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858994</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Scale Jittering">
      <data key="d0">Scale Jittering</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Scale jittering is a training technique involving random scaling of images to improve model performance by capturing multi-scale image statistics.&lt;SEP&gt;Scale jittering involves applying the model to multiple rescaled versions of a test image to improve robustness and performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Scale jittering is a testing technique that improves model performance by evaluating at multiple scales instead of a fixed size.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7bd4c026d1ee9227f8df517ef0dc9a7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13cc89ee2c4ad3ccacc469ae7d4c8d43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6368d2fa701e57fb8c2f2d07d4ed361f</data>
