    <node id="Krizhevsky">
      <data key="d0">Krizhevsky</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Krizhevsky et al. (2012) is cited as a foundational work influencing the ConvNet design principles.&lt;SEP&gt;Krizhevsky is a researcher referenced in relation to the ILSVRC-2012 competition and its neural network model.&lt;SEP&gt;Krizhevsky is an author referenced for a study in 2012 related to convolutional networks.&lt;SEP&gt;Krizhevsky is referenced as an author associated with research proposing methods to speed up ConvNet training in 2014.&lt;SEP&gt;Krizhevsky is a researcher credited with significant contributions to convolutional neural networks, notably in 2012.&lt;SEP&gt;Alex Krizhevsky is a researcher credited with advancing deep learning models for image recognition, notably in 2012.&lt;SEP&gt;Krizhevsky is an author associated with foundational work on convolutional neural networks for image recognition.</data>
