    </node>
    <node id="Convolutional Layer">
      <data key="d0">Convolutional Layer</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A convolutional layer is a component of a neural network focused on extracting features with receptive fields.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d6f4d23968c5e45cadd7773c219289a0</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858997</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Receptive Field">
      <data key="d0">Receptive Field</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">The receptive field of a filter, such as 3×3, defines the region of the input image the filter covers.&lt;SEP&gt;Receptive fields define the area of input data that influences a particular neuron in a convolutional layer.&lt;SEP&gt;Receptive fields in neural networks define the input region that affects the output of a particular neuron or layer; smaller receptive fields enable finer feature detection.&lt;SEP&gt;The area of input data influencing a particular feature, increased by padding and spatial pooling for broader context.&lt;SEP&gt;The receptive field refers to the region of the input image that a particular convolutional layer or filter can cover, affecting spatial context understanding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d6f4d23968c5e45cadd7773c219289a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7e76372644452c1c01e819997c40c4c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-416b1d89ed7672b0cd4c2753ae95d9a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ab6dde5b80886f30a7bb92c12b0d072&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbbd3487e1c203b44ae9611fe9d0a159</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774858997</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Parameter Count">
      <data key="d0">Parameter Count</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Parameter count refers to the total number of weights in a neural network, exemplified by the 144 million weights in the referenced model.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d6f4d23968c5e45cadd7773c219289a0</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
