    <node id="Image">
      <data key="d0">Image</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">The input image used in the ConvNets training process is a fixed-size RGB image of dimensions 224×224 pixels.&lt;SEP&gt;Images are the visual data used for training and testing in machine learning for image recognition.&lt;SEP&gt;The Image depicts a table illustrating the evaluation techniques for convolutional networks (ConvNets), including configuration details, evaluation methods, and error rates.&lt;SEP&gt;An image is a visual representation that undergoes rescaling and feature extraction within the described process.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bbd329f6e34d77e2545b8b6ff2369cfd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13cc89ee2c4ad3ccacc469ae7d4c8d43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ab6dde5b80886f30a7bb92c12b0d072&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b3792d8c58c852355ce9d281a964822&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-734c10ac044155da7db3e75d71944bea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-235bdad3a44d342f2586c7f9c0c1d5f2</data>
