      <data key="d0">Pre-Training Configuration</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The model was pre-trained with a fixed configuration represented by the parameter $S = 3 8 4$.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ee7c860b03e66807d924aa12f0a62399</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859003</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Object Recognition Model">
      <data key="d0">Object Recognition Model</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">The object recognition model is trained to identify objects across different scales in images.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ee7c860b03e66807d924aa12f0a62399</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859003</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ConvNet Layers">
      <data key="d0">ConvNet Layers</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">The convolutional neural network's layers are configured for regression, with specific adjustments during fine-tuning.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6d33ecd72d8316d1931ae7b8ae81c712</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859003</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Regression Type">
      <data key="d0">Regression Type</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Refers to whether the model uses Single-Class Regression (SCR) or Per-Class Regression (PCR) to predict localization.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6d33ecd72d8316d1931ae7b8ae81c712</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859003</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Localization Error">
      <data key="d0">Localization Error</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The ground-truth class localization error is a measurement of prediction accuracy for object localization in the neural network model.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6d33ecd72d8316d1931ae7b8ae81c712</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ground-Truth Class">
      <data key="d0">Ground-Truth Class</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">The true class label used as reference for measuring localization error in the model's predictions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6d33ecd72d8316d1931ae7b8ae81c712</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fine-tuned Layers">
      <data key="d0">Fine-tuned Layers</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Refers to specific layers of the neural network that are adjusted or retrained during the testing protocol, including first and second fully connected layers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6d33ecd72d8316d1931ae7b8ae81c712</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ConvNets">
      <data key="d0">ConvNets</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">ConvNets are neural network architectures widely used in the field of computer vision, increasingly considered a standard approach and being refined for better accuracy.&lt;SEP&gt;ConvNets, or Convolutional Neural Networks, are deep learning architectures used for image processing and recognition tasks, involving layers such as convolutional and pooling layers.&lt;SEP&gt;ConvNets are deep convolutional neural networks that significantly outperform previous models in image classification tasks.&lt;SEP&gt;ConvNets refers to deep convolutional neural networks used for image recognition, showing significant performance improvements.&lt;SEP&gt;ConvNets are convolutional neural networks used for image recognition, pre-trained on datasets like ILSVRC to facilitate image classification tasks on other datasets.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-668a86d65078bf8021d84fd665b305f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5619adfb7559b7fa15655e31d05a6f68&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da8ee2c8e114e5fd70e1825eda841068&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ab6dde5b80886f30a7bb92c12b0d072&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57f210dde350132bd52b55e78346cd16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1f5bdd5865b487e29cc5aa8228165cc7</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ILSVRC-2013">
      <data key="d0">ILSVRC-2013</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">ILSVRC-2013 is a computer vision challenge where various ConvNet architectures were tested and compared for image classification performance.&lt;SEP&gt;ILSVRC-2013 is an image recognition competition with notable neural network configurations and entries.&lt;SEP&gt;ILSVRC-2013 is another edition of the ImageNet Large Scale Visual Recognition Challenge, with models competing for top performance.&lt;SEP&gt;ILSVRC-2013 is a previous image recognition challenge whose winner, Overfeat, produced results less effective than VGG.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-668a86d65078bf8021d84fd665b305f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-416b1d89ed7672b0cd4c2753ae95d9a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da8ee2c8e114e5fd70e1825eda841068&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57f210dde350132bd52b55e78346cd16</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Howard">
      <data key="d0">Howard</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Howard is a researcher involved in the development of ConvNet training methods involving dense training over images and scales.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-668a86d65078bf8021d84fd665b305f7</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="3x3 Convolution Filters">
      <data key="d0">3x3 Convolution Filters</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">3x3 convolution filters are small-sized filters used uniformly across all layers to facilitate the increase of network depth without excessive computational cost.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-668a86d65078bf8021d84fd665b305f7</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Receptive Window Size">
      <data key="d0">Receptive Window Size</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Receptive window size is a parameter in convolutional neural networks that has been manipulated to improve performance in image classification tasks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-668a86d65078bf8021d84fd665b305f7</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Stride">
      <data key="d0">Stride</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Stride refers to the step size of the convolution operation, with smaller strides used to enhance neural network performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Stride of 1 pixel determines the step size for sliding filters over the image during convolution.&lt;SEP&gt;Stride specifies the step size at which the convolution filters move across the input, affecting the output size.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-668a86d65078bf8021d84fd665b305f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-416b1d89ed7672b0cd4c2753ae95d9a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ab6dde5b80886f30a7bb92c12b0d072</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dense Training">
      <data key="d0">Dense Training</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Dense training involves processing images over multiple scales and locations to improve the robustness and accuracy of convolutional networks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-668a86d65078bf8021d84fd665b305f7</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Training Time">
      <data key="d0">Training Time</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">Training time refers to the phase during which a machine learning model is trained on data, where scale jittering is applied.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-13cc89ee2c4ad3ccacc469ae7d4c8d43</data>
      <data key="d4">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d5">1774859004</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Test Time">
      <data key="d0">Test Time</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">Test time is when the trained model is evaluated on new data, with no scale jittering applied.</data>
