      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Multi-Scale Training" target="Scaling of Images">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Multi-scale training involves rescaling images based on sampled scale S to account for object size differences, improving model robustness.</data>
      <data key="d9">model robustness,scale variability</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-c221c2172115966280bf240634f365bc</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859130</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Scale S" target="Range [S_min, S_max]">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Scale S is sampled from the range [S_min, S_max], such as [256, 512], to rescale training images.</data>
      <data key="d9">parameter bounds,sampling</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-c221c2172115966280bf240634f365bc</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859129</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Scale S" target="Object in Images">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Objects of different sizes in images motivate the use of rescaling techniques like multi-scale training to enhance model performance.</data>
      <data key="d9">image rescaling,size variability</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-c221c2172115966280bf240634f365bc</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859131</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Scale S" target="Scale Q">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The scale $Q$ may differ from the training scale $S$, impacting performance.</data>
      <data key="d9">comparison,performance</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-734c10ac044155da7db3e75d71944bea</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859133</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Object in Images" target="Training">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Objects of different sizes in images motivate the multi-scale training approach to improve recognition performance.</data>
      <data key="d9">size variability</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-c221c2172115966280bf240634f365bc</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859130</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Input Image" target="Scale Q">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The input image is isotropically rescaled to the predefined smallest size $Q$.</data>
      <data key="d9">resizing,scaling</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-734c10ac044155da7db3e75d71944bea</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859131</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Input Image" target="Rescaling Scale Q">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The input image is isotropically rescaled to the size $Q$.</data>
      <data key="d9">preprocessing,resizing</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-734c10ac044155da7db3e75d71944bea</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859133</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Scale Q" target="Descriptor Stacking">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Scaling factors Q = {2, 5, 6}, {3, 8, 4}, and {5, 1, 2} are used in descriptor stacking for multiscale feature extraction.</data>
      <data key="d9">data analysis,scale-specific representations</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-910b19d5d7e003782ec85519b01d0c2b</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859496</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Fully-Connected Layers" target="Convolutional Layers">
      <data key="d7">2.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The convolutional layers are followed by three fully-connected layers in the neural network architecture.&lt;SEP&gt;Fully-connected layers are converted to convolutional layers for dense application.</data>
      <data key="d9">architecture,network conversion,sequence</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-734c10ac044155da7db3e75d71944bea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23eb0012359dac75ed79e6c991260f55</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859131</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Fully-Connected Layers" target="ILSVRC Classification">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The third fully-connected layer performs classification for ILSVRC with 1000 channels.</data>
      <data key="d9">function</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-23eb0012359dac75ed79e6c991260f55</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859238</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Fully-Connected Layers" target="Soft-Max Layer">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The soft-max layer acts as the final classification layer, converting outputs into class probabilities.</data>
      <data key="d9">role</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-23eb0012359dac75ed79e6c991260f55</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859239</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Fully-Connected Layers" target="Neural Networks">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The three fully-connected layers follow the convolutional layers, with specified channel counts.</data>
      <data key="d9">architecture,layer sequence</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-23eb0012359dac75ed79e6c991260f55</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859240</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Convolutional Layers" target="Class Score Map">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The convolutional layers produce a class score map with spatial resolution.</data>
      <data key="d9">output,processing</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-734c10ac044155da7db3e75d71944bea</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859132</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Convolutional Layers" target="Neural Networks">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Convolutional layers serve as the initial layered components in the neural network architecture, setting the foundation for feature extraction.</data>
      <data key="d9">architecture,layer sequence</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-23eb0012359dac75ed79e6c991260f55</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859240</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Convolutional Layers" target="ConvNets">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Convolutional layers utilize filters like 3×3 and 1×1 to extract features from images.</data>
      <data key="d9">architecture,feature extraction</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-0ab6dde5b80886f30a7bb92c12b0d072</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859421</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Convolutional Layers" target="Filters">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Convolutional layers apply filters like 3×3 or 1×1 to extract or transform features from input images.</data>
      <data key="d9">feature detection,feature transformation</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-0ab6dde5b80886f30a7bb92c12b0d072</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859422</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Convolutional Layers" target="Padding">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Padding of 1 pixel in convolutional layers helps maintain the input's spatial resolution after convolutions.</data>
      <data key="d9">spatial resolution</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-0ab6dde5b80886f30a7bb92c12b0d072</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859422</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Convolutional Layers" target="Receptive Field">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Filters with small receptive fields, such as 3×3, are used to capture local features like edges and textures.</data>
      <data key="d9">Feature Detection</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-0ab6dde5b80886f30a7bb92c12b0d072</data>
      <data key="d11">Very_Deep_Convolutional_Networks_for_Large-Scale_Image_Recognition_content_list.json</data>
      <data key="d12">1774859424</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Convolutional Layers" target="Stride">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
